				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Think about it for a bit, especially with /pet no spell AA.
<br />

<br />
Do we really need the water pet for raw damage? It's mostly situational, from the rear, on some boss mobs, kiting and some xp groups.
<br />
What's mage's biggest problem? *LFG*...
<br />

<br />
Would it help if we can offer a "sort-of" healer to groups?
<br />
Set the pet to melee like earth pet, not such high DPs, but it acts as a cleric = lvl of caster of ye fire pet (*cough*).
<br />

<br />
Think about it for a bit, also about possible improvements to NPC AI.
<br />

<br />
Would you rather have high damage water pet that doesn't tank well, doesn't get you groups though.
<br />
Or cleric pet? Or perhaps some form of pet that heals the group by a proc, recourse or like?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304331" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: red">REDORIOUS.....ARCHMAGE.....KARANA</span></span></a>
