What I would like to see is 4 special AA that will affect our current pets and will make them more effective in their current evironment...
<br />

<br />
1) "Reposition" - Water Pet
<br />
This AA gives the waterr pet the ability to go to the back of the mob every 10 seconds if its not behind them already.
<br />

<br />
2) "Snaring Roots" - Earth Pet
<br />
This AA changes the root to snare (low duration) on the eath pets
<br />

<br />
3) "Specialization" - Fire Pet
<br />
This adds 3 new commands to the fire pet.  /pet Nuke, /Pet Buff, /Pet Combo.  One command only lets the pet cast various DD stuff.  One allows it to just use beneifical spells on group (not itself) and the third is for it to make a combo of the other two.
<br />

<br />
4) "Hurricane" - Air Pet
<br />
This gives the air pet a longer stun ability that does a little more damage than the one it uses now...would also increase its melee damage output by 10%.
<br />

<br />
I think we would see appropriate uses for all of our pets...Water in groups for DPS, Air to solo in some situations, Earth to solo in others or group when no snarer, Fire in groups for some DD and Buffage.  All would have their place and it would prevent me from casting my Air pet 90% and Water pet 10% of the time....I miss the old hunk of poo.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
