				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Want a healer? Ignore me, get a cleric or druid, hell, I don't want to be a healer. Giving me or my pet general heals is bazarre and totally inappropriate for our class IMO ... we are magi, not clerics, and we shouldnt be looking for groups as healers of any kind. But need DAMAGE? Then pick me! If I am LFG too much, my damage (or perceived damage) must not be high enough, so look there for your "fix", if one is needed, I suggest.
<br />

<br />
Some of Pyrov's ideas are nice, in that they are not overpowered and they fit with the concept of the Magician class.
<br />

<br />
The "Position" idea for Water Pets I really like, I mean, we all do it anyway, but it takes it to the next level for experienced magi. The AA would probably be pretty expensive, but I love the idea. Given pathing issues though, I bet it would be messy and/or difficult to implement. But who knows. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
The 100% snare to replace root for Earth Pets has been discussed elsewhere. Certainly not overpowering, but it makes us a little more group friendly with earth pets, so nice idea.
<br />

<br />
The Air Pet suggestion is not so great IMO. Personally I love the Air Pet's abilities exactly as they are now, and they don't really need an upgrade per se. Compared to other mage pets, Air Pet DPS feels about right. Part of this suggestion tho reads like a general "DPS upgrade" request. That is not an air pet specific issue I feel, but rather the more general "balance pets DPS" issue that this thread doesn't seem to be about. 
<br />

<br />
I don't like the group buffing idea for Fire Pets at all, however. Again, we are not buffers, that's the job of other classes (except group DS). The Fire Pet tho is a mess; giving control over the spells it can and can't cast from its current list might help ... a little ... maybe. I doubt I'd use it anyway tho, it's just too weak.
<br />

<br />
Suzanna.<br />_________________<br />Arch Convoker Suzanna Dreamingheart
